# LECTURE 7:
# ==========
#
# LAUNCHING THE BASIC PYTHON INTERPRETER:
# =======================================
# To launch the basic Python interpreter from the shell command
# line, invoke

python

# Type Ctrl+D to exit the basic Python interpreter

# LAUNCHING THE IPYTHON INTERPRETER:
# ==================================
# To launch the IPython interpreter from the shell command line,
# invoke

ipython

# Type Ctrl+D to exit the basic Python interpreter

# LAUNCHING AN IPYTHON NOTEBOOK SESSION:
# ======================================
# To launch the IPython Notebook session from the shell command
# line, invoke

ipython notebook

# This will launch a background IPython session, start a lightweight
# webserver that communicates with the IPython session, then launch a
# web browser and connect to the webserver.